      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "1513b812e9580127",
        "text": "This contingency leads to the fact that freedom becomes the indispensable reference value of power. Only where freedom prevails does power come into play. \"Power presupposes freedom\" (39). Therefore, it is crucial for the medium of power not to damage this condition of its possibility. For this reason, power is essentially threatening power: alter and ego each exchange arguments as to why it is advisable or not to adopt a course of action, and depending on who puts forward the better arguments, which by no means merely claim reasonableness for themselves, one wins this power game. The motives for giving in and giving in are often negative sanctions, which are threatened but are not used if possible. Luhmann therefore also speaks of the zero methodology of power, since the possibilities of punishment in the case of rejection of the action requirement, ultimately the use of force, are brought into play, but without this move actually being carried out."
